{"sequence":20,"timestamp":"2026-04-30T22:41:36.572725991Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-dfd6c407","body":"`src/test_support/drain_harness.rs:272` implements the whole drain dependency surface directly as a `DrainPort`, and the key steps are canned at that same boundary (`create_project_from_bead` at `src/test_support/drain_harness.rs:315`, `open_pr` at `src/test_support/drain_harness.rs:393`, `watch_pr` at `src/test_support/drain_harness.rs:408`). This means the new harness does not exercise the library entry points/ports that this bead is meant to integrate: project creation, PR opening/gates/squash, PR watching/rerun/merge, and bead mutation are all simulated above those modules. A regression in the production wiring from `ralph drain` into `create_project_from_bead`, `open_pr_for_completed_run`, or `watch_pr` would not fail these tests. Fix the harness so it uses the real drain module entry points with lower-level mocks for br/git/PR/watch/run, or add a separate scenario that wires those production entry points together with mock ports rather than replacing them with a coarse `DrainPort` fake.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"ecfb8c65b03acb173656d4d4ac7abac1981448d904418d58d97936d1e90fca5b","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260430215610","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":21,"timestamp":"2026-04-30T22:41:36.590804907Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-794d0617","body":"`tests/unit/drain_harness_test.rs:92` names the backend-exhausted case as a skip-and-continue scenario, but it creates only one bead and then accepts `DrainOutcome::Drained { cycles: 1 }` at `tests/unit/drain_harness_test.rs:103`. That would still pass if skip handling closed the current bead and then stopped without processing subsequent ready work. Add a second ready happy-path bead to this scenario and assert the first bead is in `report.skipped`, the second lands, and the report has two cycles, so the `SkipBeadAndContinueDrain` recovery action is actually covered by the harness.","classification":"fix_current_bead","dedup_key":"ab6b47663d34b4212314765755de4b50eaeabaeb1b3ea87561abcad6d68155fc","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.5-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260430215610","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
